Preheat #oven{} to 400 degrees (if you have a microwave you can skip this!). Chop the @cilantro{1%bunch}. Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Halve, peel, and finely chop half the @red onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Peel the @mango{1} with a #peeler{}. Cut around the flat seed then into 1/4-inch slices. Cut the slices into thick strips to create matchsticks.

> For more tips on how to work with mangoes, visit: Blog.HelloFresh.com

== Lime Crema ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, lime zest, and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

== Mango Slaw ==

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together the mango, red onion, cilantro, juice of the remaining lime, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

== Chicken ==

Butterfly the @chicken breasts{2}: with one hand on top of the breast, carefully slice into the breast parallel to your hand. Stop before cutting all the way through. Then, open it up like a book and season with salt and pepper on both sides.

Rub or brush both sides of the butterflied chicken with 1 tablespoon of adobo (the sauce in the can of @chipotles in adobo{1%can}). Careful, it's spicy! Set aside and reserve chipotle peppers for another time!

Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and cook ~{5-7%minutes} per side, until slightly charred and cooked through.

== Assembly ==

While the chicken cooks, wrap the @flour tortilla{6} in #aluminum foil{} and place in the oven for ~{5%minutes} to warm. Alternately, wrap the tortillas in a damp #paper towel{} and microwave on high for ~{30%seconds}. Halve, pit, and scoop out the @avocado{1} flesh into a small bowl. Mash with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice the chicken. Spread the mashed avocado onto the tortillas and top with the chicken, mango slaw, and lime crema.

Serve the tacos with the remaining mango slaw to the side. Enjoy!